org.bladerunnerjs.model

Interface AssetLocation

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BRJSNode, Node
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    RootAssetLocation, TestAssetLocation, ThemedAssetLocation
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractChildSourceAssetLocation, AbstractDeepAssetLocation, AbstractShallowAssetLocation, AbstractSourceAssetLocation, BladeResourcesAssetLocation, BRJSConformantJsLibRootAssetLocation, BRJSConformantRootAssetLocation, ChildSourceAssetLocation, ChildTestSourceAssetLocation, NullAssetLocation, ResourcesAssetLocation, SourceAssetLocation, TestSourceAssetLocation, TheAbstractAssetLocation, ThirdpartyAssetLocation

    public interface AssetLocation
extends BRJSNode
    Represents the parent directory of any AssetFile, so in the example src/a/b/c/someFile.xml it would represent the src/a/b/c directory. Due to legacy resources the AssetLocation for any file in resources is always the resources directory. So in the example resources/a/b/c/someFile.xml, resouces is the AssetLocation.
